From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Ammar <ammar@example.com>
Date: Thu, 3 Jul 2026 00:00:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] failed_status: make mark_status_failed race-safe via savepoint

mark_status_failed implemented its upsert as update-then-insert against the
(revision, status_name) primary key. Under an obsolete storm -- many builds for
the same revision obsoleted by a newer commit at once -- concurrent calls all
observe rowcount==0 on the update and all insert; the loser raises
IntegrityError on the PK. Since the insert runs inside the caller's transaction
that exception poisons it and propagates as "Got fatal Exception on DB",
aborting the build-stop path. The build record freezes in "running" and the
worker slot leaks; after four leaks every virtual worker is busy and CI
deadlocks (observed in production on theoden, 2026-07-02).

Guard the insert with a SAVEPOINT (conn.begin_nested). On a PK collision roll
back only the savepoint, leaving the outer transaction usable so the build-stop
path completes and no slot leaks. The winning caller still writes the row, so
the bookkeeping stays correct.

Stopgap for nix-community/buildbot-nix (pin 0c1190ae); bug still present on
upstream HEAD 2026-06-28, no upstream issue yet.

---
 buildbot_nix/db/failed_status.py | 12 ++++++++++--
 1 file changed, 10 insertions(+), 2 deletions(-)

--- a/buildbot_nix/db/failed_status.py
+++ b/buildbot_nix/db/failed_status.py
@@ -6,6 +6,7 @@
 from typing import TYPE_CHECKING

 import sqlalchemy as sa
+from sqlalchemy.exc import IntegrityError
 from buildbot.db import base

 if TYPE_CHECKING:
@@ -62,14 +63,25 @@
                 )
                 result = conn.execute(update_stmt)

-                # If no rows were updated, insert a new one
+                # If no rows were updated, insert a new one. Guard the insert
+                # with a savepoint so a concurrent insert for the same
+                # (revision, status_name) during an obsolete storm cannot abort
+                # the outer transaction: under that race both callers see
+                # rowcount==0, both insert, and the loser hits the PK. Rolling
+                # back only the savepoint keeps the build-stop path alive and
+                # prevents the worker slot from leaking.
                 if result.rowcount == 0:
                     insert_stmt = self.failed_statuses.insert().values(
                         revision=revision,
                         status_name=status_name,
                         timestamp=timestamp,
                     )
-                    conn.execute(insert_stmt)
+                    savepoint = conn.begin_nested()
+                    try:
+                        conn.execute(insert_stmt)
+                        savepoint.commit()
+                    except IntegrityError:
+                        savepoint.rollback()

                 trans.commit()
             except Exception:
